{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:41.131875+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 0106df7cae53ded949745c853fa30cbf79ffb0c6)", "id": "lc_44940d27-3d41-45e4-84fb-704905d25a75"}, {"type": "text", "text": "[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"gwc\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\ndescription = \"Git Workflow Companion — small, local-only git helpers\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nlicense = { text = \"MIT\" }\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = []\n\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\"src\"]\n", "id": "lc_d0d093b2-0aa3-4293-b694-41d1b059439f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "8ef1522f-d3b9-4dc5-b8eb-fa15953ef6fe", "tool_call_id": "call_00_QdeRq7ibdq3MDkFb03Ju8234", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:47.171371+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 557, "prompt_tokens": 7753, "total_tokens": 8310, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 204, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7552}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7552, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 201}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "879efb02-88a8-4706-ad8f-4ce0d7f7d71e", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f6-7f0c-7ce0-95af-190551f782e3-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T09_R01_C03_A03", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Hi @BruceKZ, thanks for checking out `gwc`!\n\n`gwc` is deliberately scoped to local-only git workflow helpers — network operations like `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope. This is documented both in the README's [Not supported](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T09_R01_C03_A03/blob/main/README.md#not-supported) section and in the intro paragraph:\n\n> *Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.*\n\nSo `gwc push` is not a command that was removed — it was never added, by design. The idea is that `gwc` handles opinionated shortcuts around local branch management and status, while you always use plain `git` for anything that touches a remote.\n\nWe wouldn't want to blur that boundary, so adding `push` (or any other network command) is not something we plan to support. I'd recommend just using `git push` directly.\n\nClosing this as **not planned** since it's an intentional design constraint. Thanks for the interest though!"}, "id": "call_00_5U6iQwesljXou7hE5j9D8155", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7753, "output_tokens": 557, "total_tokens": 8310, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7552}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 204}}}}]}}}
